# Ownership boundaries

Agents must **not** modify files outside their assigned ownership unless the user or planner **explicitly** asks for a cross-cutting integration change.

| Own | Path |
|-----|------|
| Mobile | `apps/mobile/**` |
| Vision API | `services/vision-api/**` |
| Contracts | `packages/contracts/**` |
| Docs / meta | `docs/**`, `TASKS.md`, root `README.md`, `.cursor/rules/**` |

**Allowed cross-touch examples (only when instructed):** bump `@roadcopilot/contracts` import paths, add a shared env example line, fix a broken workspace reference.

**Not allowed:** rewriting another app’s business logic “while you’re here,” or moving files between owners without instruction.

When a feature needs another area, **describe the contract** (types, endpoint, behavior) and hand off instead of editing their tree silently.
